<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 093.11141/23.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 303
                            of the 29th ultimo, covering a copy of a note from the Foreign Office
                            making formal acceptance on the part of the British Government of the
                            gift of a replica of Houdon’s statue of Washington offered by the State
                            of Virginia.</p>
                        <p>It has afforded the Department pleasure to communicate copies of your
                            despatch and of its enclosure to the Governor of Virginia with reference
                            to the previous correspondence.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>